<li><a href="http://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/Pub1106_scr.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/Pub1106_scr.pdf" rel="nofollow">The criticality accident in Sarov</a>, <a href="/wiki/International_Atomic_Energy_Agency" title="International Atomic Energy Agency">International Atomic Energy Agency</a>, 2001 — well documented account of the biological effects of a criticality accident</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bt.cdc.gov/radiation/arsphysicianfactsheet.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.bt.cdc.gov/radiation/arsphysicianfactsheet.asp" rel="nofollow">The Center for Disease Control's fact sheet on Acute Radiation Syndrome</a></li>
<li><a href="http://courses.cs.vt.edu/~cs3604/lib/Therac_25/Therac_1.html" class="external text" title="http://courses.cs.vt.edu/~cs3604/lib/Therac_25/Therac_1.html" rel="nofollow">Therac-25 computerized radiation therapy machine accidents</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.bomb-shelter.net/nuclear-weapons" class="external text" title="http://www.bomb-shelter.net/nuclear-weapons" rel="nofollow">50-KT to 1-MT surface burst thermal burns and radiation doses</a></li>
</ul>
